import EconCSLib.Foundations.Graph
import EconCSLib.Foundations.Math
import EconCSLib.Foundations.Optimization
import EconCSLib.Foundations.Probability
import EconCSLib.Foundations.Econometrics

/-!
# EconCSLib Foundations

Aggregate import for paper-independent mathematical foundations.

## Main declarations

- `EconCSLib.Foundations.Math`: finite sums/rankings/rounding, asymptotics,
  continuity, and elementary real-analysis helpers.
- `EconCSLib.Foundations.Graph`: graph and cycle primitives.
- `EconCSLib.Foundations.Optimization`: finite argmax, finite feasible search,
  linear-expectation decision interfaces, and feasible-set optimality
  certificates.
- `EconCSLib.Foundations.Probability`: finite PMFs, kernels, conditional
  probability, measure inequalities, sampling, stochastic processes,
  admissions/testing wrappers, order-statistic interfaces, and
  large-deviation certificates.
- `EconCSLib.Foundations.Econometrics`: rating-model primitives.
-/
